(472,'gliscor',179,20,425,'It glides soundlessly on pitch-black wings and sinks sharp fangs into the throat of its prey. It takes on a look of satisfaction once it has entirely drained its prey of blood.'),
(473,'mamoswine',265,25,2910,'This species reached its zenith during the period known as the ice age. I suspect that Hisui’s frigid climate is in harmony with Mamoswine’s constitution, thus awakening hidden potential.'),
(474,'porygon-z',268,9,340,'A curious item induced this evolution. The Pokémon’s offensive capabilities have greatly increased, but the strangeness of its behavior has magnified in equal measure. This worries me.'),
(475,'gallade',259,16,520,'The blades extending from its elbows are sharper than the finest swords. Its swordsmanship, albeit self-taught, is astonishingly impressive.'),
(476,'probopass',184,14,3400,'It is able to emit powerful magnetism, allowing it control over the iron sand that forms its luscious mustache. Using this iron sand, Probopass forms hard stones with which it smites its prey.'),
(477,'dusknoir',263,22,1066,'Comes to those whose lives have come to an end and escorts their souls to the afterlife. Known to mistakenly take the souls of those who yet have life left in them, albeit rarely.'),
(478,'froslass',168,13,266,'A Pokémon inhabited by the soul of a woman who died bearing a grudge in the snowy mountains. Legends of Froslass placing deathly curses on misbehaving men send shivers down my spine.'),
(479,'rotom',154,3,3,'This bizarre Pokémon appears to be a will-o’-the-wisp powered by electricity. Be wary, as Rotom is both smart and mischievous.'),
(480,'uxie',290,3,3,'A Pokémon feared but also respected for stealing away the memories of evildoers. I have found records that suggest Uxie holds dominion over knowledge.'),
(481,'mesprit',290,3,3,'Known as the Being of Emotion. In legend, this Pokémon was feared, as any who showed disrespect would have their emotions thrown into disarray.'),
(482,'azelf',290,3,3,'The dreaded Being of Willpower. Legends tell of this Pokémon manipulating the will of its adversaries and turning them into puppets of its own.'),
(483,'dialga',340,54,6830,'This Pokémon is revered as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Dialga was what caused the vast river of time to begin flowing in our world.'),
(484,'palkia',340,42,3360,'This Pokémon is feared as a deity in Hisuian legend. The birth of Palkia was what caused the walls of our world to disappear, creating a sky that spans for infinity.'),
(485,'heatran',300,17,4300,'Stories tell of this Pokémon being birthed from the boiling magma within Mount Coronet. Its molten-steel body holds many mysteries.'),
(486,'regigigas',335,37,4200,'According to legend, Regigigas pulled landmasses together and bound them with rope to create the continent of Hisui. Though I have my doubts, the story could well contain a shred of truth.'),
(487,'giratina-altered',340,45,7500,'There is one Hisuian verse that tells of a powerful light creating a deep shadow. I imagine that this deep shadow is Giratina.'),
(488,'cresselia',300,15,856,'Cresselia is reminiscent of the crescent moon. It leaves a brilliant line of light in its wake as it flies across the night sky. I daresay it resembles the heavenly maiden who created the Milky Way.'),
(489,'phione',216,4,31,'Can be seen floating offshore during seasons when the seas are warm. Its azure body blends in with the ocean waters—logic suggests this is a defense mechanism against natural predators.'),
(490,'manaphy',270,3,14,'Rumored to migrate across the oceans and visit Hisui’s coastal waters only rarely. Although Manaphy resembles Phione, it is also quite different. The relation between the two is unclear.'),
(491,'darkrai',270,15,505,'On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village’s inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.'),
(492,'shaymin-land',270,2,21,'When the turning of seasons brings the cruel winter to its end and the joyous people give thanks to the heavens, Shaymin appears and covers the withered land with flowers.'),
(493,'arceus',324,32,3200,'It is the heavenly fount from which pours the light that shines across Hisui. Its luminance guides and protects all Pokémon. Hisuian mythology states that Arceus is the creator of all things.'),
(494,'victini',300,4,40,'When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.'),
(495,'snivy',62,6,81,'They photosynthesize by bathing their tails in sunlight. When they are not feeling well, their tails droop.'),
(496,'servine',145,8,160,'When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.'),
(497,'serperior',238,33,630,'It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.'),
(498,'tepig',62,5,99,'It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.'),
(499,'pignite',146,10,555,'When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.'),
(500,'emboar',238,16,1500,'It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.'),
(501,'oshawott',62,5,59,'This Pokémon from the Unova region uses the shell on its belly as a weapon to cut down its foes. Thus, I’ve conferred upon this shell the name “scalchop.”'),
(502,'dewott',145,8,245,'Its exquisite double-scalchop technique is likely the result of daily training, and it can send even masters of the blade fleeing in defeat.'),
(503,'samurott',238,15,946,'One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.'),
(504,'patrat',51,5,116,'Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.'),
(505,'watchog',147,11,270,'When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.'),
(506,'lillipup',55,4,41,'This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won’t forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.'),
(507,'herdier',130,9,147,'The black fur that covers this Pokémon’s body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.'),
(508,'stoutland',250,12,610,'Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It’s said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.'),
(509,'purrloin',56,4,101,'Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.'),
(510,'liepard',156,11,375,'This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.'),
(511,'pansage',63,6,105,'It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.'),
(512,'simisage',174,11,305,'Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.'),
(513,'pansear',63,6,110,'This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.'),
(514,'simisear',174,10,280,'When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.'),
(515,'panpour',63,6,135,'The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.'),
(516,'simipour',174,10,290,'It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.'),
(517,'munna',58,6,233,'It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it’s eating a good dream, and black when it’s eating a nightmare.'),
(518,'musharna',170,11,605,'It drowses and dreams all the time. It’s best to leave it be if it’s just woken up, as it’s a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.'),
(519,'pidove',53,3,21,'It’s forgetful and not very bright, but many Trainers love it anyway for its friendliness and sincerity.'),
(520,'tranquill',125,6,150,'These bright Pokémon have acute memories. Apparently delivery workers often choose them as their partners.'),
(521,'unfezant',244,12,290,'Males have plumage on their heads. They will never let themselves feel close to anyone other than their Trainers.'),
(522,'blitzle',59,8,298,'Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.'),
(523,'zebstrika',174,16,795,'They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.'),
(524,'roggenrola',56,4,180,'When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.'),
(525,'boldore',137,9,1020,'It relies on sound in order to monitor what’s in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it’s facing.'),
(526,'gigalith',258,17,2600,'Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck, they have a limitation— they can only be fired when the sun is out.'),
(527,'woobat',65,4,21,'It emits ultrasonic waves as it flutters about, searching for its prey—bug Pokémon.'),
(528,'swoobat',149,9,105,'The auspicious shape of this Pokémon’s nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.'),
(529,'drilbur',66,3,85,'It’s a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.'),
(530,'excadrill',178,7,404,'Known as the Drill King, this Pokémon can tunnel through the terrain at speeds of over 90 mph.'),
(531,'audino',390,11,310,'This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures’ feelings and physical conditions.'),
(532,'timburr',61,6,125,'Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.'),
(533,'gurdurr',142,12,400,'Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there’s skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.'),
(534,'conkeldurr',253,14,870,'When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.'),
(535,'tympole',59,5,45,'It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can’t hear its cries of warning.'),
(536,'palpitoad',134,8,170,'On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.'),
(537,'seismitoad',255,15,620,'This Pokémon is popular among the elderly, who say the vibrations of its lumps are great for massages.'),
(538,'throh',163,13,555,'They train in groups of five. Any member that can’t keep up will discard its belt and leave the group.'),
(539,'sawk',163,14,510,'The karate chops of a Sawk that’s trained itself to the limit can cleave the ocean itself.'),
(540,'sewaddle',62,3,25,'Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.'),
(541,'swadloon',133,5,73,'It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.'),
(542,'leavanny',225,12,205,'It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.'),
(543,'venipede',52,4,53,'Its fangs are highly venomous. If this Pokémon finds prey it thinks it can eat, it leaps for them without any thought of how things might turn out.'),
(544,'whirlipede',126,12,585,'Whirlipede protects itself with a sturdy shell and poisonous spikes while it stores up the energy it’ll need for evolution.'),
(545,'scolipede',243,25,2005,'Scolipede engage in fierce territorial battles with Centiskorch. At the end of one of these battles, the victor makes a meal of the loser.'),
(546,'cottonee',56,3,6,'Weaving together the cotton of both Cottonee and Eldegoss produces exquisite cloth that’s highly prized by many luxury brands.'),
(547,'whimsicott',168,7,66,'As long as this Pokémon bathes in sunlight, its cotton keeps growing. If too much cotton fluff builds up, Whimsicott tears it off and scatters it.'),
(548,'petilil',56,5,66,'The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.'),
(549,'lilligant',168,11,163,'Essential oils made from Lilligant flowers have a sublime scent, but they’re also staggeringly expensive.'),
